{
  "texts": [
    "While the RAG approach aims to enhance factual accuracy by incorporating external information, it also exposes the model to the biases present in the data sources.",
    "Ensuring that the retrieval process is fair and unbiased is essential to maintain the integrity of the generated responses.",
    "Future research should focus on developing techniques to identify and mitigate biases in the retrieval process, thereby enhancing the fairness and reliability of RAG-augmented LLMs.",
    "Additionally, further studies should explore the integration of more sophisticated retrieval algorithms and data filtering techniques to improve the quality of the retrieved information.",
    "ConclusionThe research presented in this paper has provided a comprehensive exploration of augmenting the Llama model with a reverse proxy-style Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) mechanism to enhance factual accuracy and coherence."
  ]
}